  "slug": "french-toast-roll-ups",
  "title": "French Toast Roll Ups",
  "subtitle": "Crisp cinnamon rolls made from flattened white bread",
  "excerpt": "French Toast Roll Ups. A home-cook's recipe from Rebecca's collection, kept in the family rotation.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook. A modern North American variation on French toast, adapted for a finger-food format popular at brunches and with children.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "French toast roll-ups are slices of white bread rolled thin, spread with a cinnamon butter filling, rolled into cylinders, dipped in egg, and fried until golden. Finished with a cinnamon-sugar coating while still hot. Makes 8 rolls in about 20 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Use soft, fresh sandwich bread; it flattens without tearing. Roll each slice firmly so the cylinder holds its shape during frying. Cook in batches so the pan stays hot and the outside crisps rather than steams.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
